==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Morocco
<hw>Mo*roc"co</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named from
<ets>Morocco</ets>, the country. Cf. <er>Morris</er> the dance.]</ety>
<def>A fine kind of leather, prepared commonly from goatskin (though an
inferior kind is made of sheepskin), and tanned with sumac and dyed of
various colors; -- said to have been first made by the Moors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morology</ent>⟦br⟧
